      • rangeQueryLocal

        public static <S extends Shape> long rangeQueryLocal(org.apache.hadoop.fs.Path inPath,
                                     Shape queryRange,
                                     S shape,
                                     OperationsParams params,
                                     ResultCollector<S> output)
                            throws IOException,
                                   InterruptedException
        Runs a range query on the local machine (no MapReduce) and the output is streamed to the provided result collector. The query might run in parallel which makes it necessary to design the result collector to accept parallel calls to the method ResultCollector.collect(Object). You can use ResultCollectorSynchronizer to synchronize calls to your ResultCollector if you cannot design yours to be thread safe.
